            "title": "The Fermenter",
            "text": "A 2x2x2 fermenter."
        },
        {
            "type": "patchouli:text",
            "text": "The Fermenter is a multiblock that allows you to... well ferment stuff. It can be built from size 1x2x1 all the way up to 3x3x3, and always needs a control panel as well as an airlock. The Fermenter has an internal temperature, which is affected by the environment and powered heaters."
        },
        {
            "type": "patchouli:text",
            "text": "Some recipes also need mixing, in which case a powered mixer is required.$(br2)A recipe consists of five steps, which have different conditions:$(li)Time spent in this step should be in a given range$(li)Temperature during this step should be in a given range$(li)The brew must, or must not, be mixed during this step"
        },
        {
            "type": "patchouli:text",
            "text": "Fermenting recipe steps follow two rules:$(li)if the next step's conditions are met and enough time has been spent in this step, complete the current step.$(li)if the current step's conditions are not met, the recipe fails after a grace period.$()"
        },
